**************************************************************************************
    Automatic gear shifting system using arduino, relais, bluetooth module and smartphone.
    
    The idea is, that the shifting systems switches gears automatically in respective
    to a given target crank frequency and the current velocity. The system detects if
    the measured crank freqency is bigger than the target crank frequency and shifts up
    or shifts down if a lower crank frequency is measured.
    
    By a separate developed smartphone App it is possible to control the shifting system
    via bluetooth, by setting the target crank frequency, setting the allowed frequency
    divergence, setting the wheel size and sending a RESET - signal to the system.
    The App also can be used as a control view, as it also displayes the current velocity,
    the current crank frequency and the current front and rear gear.

    Velocity - measurement:
    Measuring the time between two peeks of the reed sensor at the front wheel. Equals time
    of one round of wheel.
    
    velocity = wheelCircumference[mm] / time[ms] * 3.6 = km/h
    crankFrequency = 60000 / (Zeit[ms] * gear ration(current gear)) = U/min
    
    Number of teeth of front and rear  chainblades are stored in seperated Arrays. 
    Front: Small Chainblade is left and therefor no. 1 in Array.
    Rear: Biggest is left and therefor no. 1 in Array.
    Shifting up can be done by simply increase a position in either array. 
    -> means currentFront++ is shifting to a bigger gear the same way as
    currentRear-- is shifting down and the other way round.
    
    To prevent wearing out the mechanics we decided to not use the gears 1-9, 1-10, 2-1, 2-2,
    where the first digit is front chainblade and second is rear chainblade.
    
    To avoid unnecessary shift operations we choose the following plan to shift gears:
    Shifting up: 1-1, 1-2, .... , 1-8, 2-4, 2-5, .... , 2-10,
    Shifting down: 2-10, 2-9, .... , 2-3, 1-7, 1-6, .... , 1-1
    
    We decided to write a "void generateSignal(int count, int mode)" Methode. 
    count = the number of gears one wants to shift
    mode: 1 = front up, 2 = front down, 3 = rear up, 4 = rear down  
    
    Connections at arduino:
    Arduino <--> Relais:
        VCC -- 5V
        IN4 -- Pin 8  (rear up)
        IN3 -- Pin 12 (rear down)
        IN2 -- Pin 4  (front up)
        IN1 -- Pin 7  (front down)
    Arduino <--> board:
        TX(bluetooth) -- Pin 10
        RX(bluetooth) -- Pin 11
        Velocity senor pin -- Pin 2
        crank frequency sensor pin -- Pin 3
    Relais <--> shifting system(bike)
        Connect the wires of the back shifting to the left pins, from left to right:
        (free) red blue (free) green yellow
        
        Connect the wires of the front shifting to the right pins, from left to right:
        (free) red blue (free) green yellow
